{"result":"The `astro-mermaid` integration offers several configuration options to control the appearance, theme behavior, logging, and icon packs for Mermaid diagrams. These options are passed as an object of type `AstroMermaidOptions` to the `mermaid()` integration function in your `astro.config.mjs` file.  

## Configuration Options

Here are the available configuration options for `astro-mermaid` and what each one does:

### `theme`
This option sets the initial Mermaid theme for rendering diagrams.  It accepts one of the following string values: `'default'`, `'dark'`, `'forest'`, `'neutral'`, or `'base'`.  The default value is `'default'`.  If `autoTheme` is enabled, this value can be overridden by a detected system or site theme. 

### `autoTheme`
When set to `true`, this boolean option enables automatic theme switching.  The integration monitors the `data-theme` attribute on the `<html>` or `<body>` elements and automatically switches the Mermaid theme to `'dark'` if the attribute is `dark`, and to `'default'` (or the configured `theme`) otherwise.  The default value for `autoTheme` is `true`. 

### `enableLog`
This boolean option controls whether the client-side script outputs initialization and rendering logs to the browser console.  Critical errors are always logged regardless of this setting.  The default value is `true`. 

### `mermaidConfig`
This option is a pass-through object for native Mermaid API configuration, allowing fine-grained control over specific diagram types.  It is of type `Record<string, any>` and defaults to an empty object `{}`.  For example, you can configure flowchart curve styles within this object.  The integration validates this object to prevent prototype pollution by forbidding keys like `__proto__`, `constructor`, and `prototype`.  

### `iconPacks`
This option is an array of `IconPack` definitions used to register icon packs for `architecture-beta` diagrams.  The default value is an empty array `[]`.  Each `IconPack` object can have the following properties:
*   `name`: A string representing the prefix used to reference icons (e.g., `logos:aws`). 
*   `url`: A string providing the direct URL to the Iconify JSON file. This is the preferred method for serialization. 
*   `loader`: A function that fetches the JSON. This is a legacy option, and the integration extracts the URL via regex at build time. It is recommended to use the `url` property instead for safer serialization. 

The `iconPacks` are processed during the `astro:config:setup` hook, where the integration extracts the URL from either the `url` property or the `loader` function (if provided) and serializes it for client-side use. 

## Example Configuration

You can configure `astro-mermaid` in your `astro.config.mjs` file like this:


```js
// astro.config.mjs
import { defineConfig } from 'astro/config';
import mermaid from 'astro-mermaid';

export default defineConfig({
  integrations: [
    mermaid({
      theme: 'forest',
      autoTheme: true,
      enableLog: false,
      mermaidConfig: {
        flowchart: {
          curve: 'basis'
        }
      },
      iconPacks: [
        {
          name: 'logos',
          loader: () => fetch('https://unpkg.com/@iconify-json/logos@1/icons.json').then(res => res.json())
        }
      ]
    })
  ]
});
```  

## Notes

The `astro-mermaid` integration also checks for the presence of `@mermaid-js/layout-elk` in your project dependencies to conditionally enable ELK layout support.  

